The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, March 15, 2004 				 Staging the life of Vivekananda
																								Shilpkaar presents a musical monoact tracing the life of one of the greatest modern ascetics that India has known, that of Swami Vivekanada. The city will have the pleasure of witnessing a masterly act by the versatile Shekhar Sen who enacts the life of the Swamiji with aesthetic precision. This play traces Vivekanandas journey through life as a man who surrenders his very existence to the cause of the Almighty and takes upon himself the responsibility of educating mankind on the tangibility of goodness and virtue. Sens Vivekananda is a genius who conquers the world with words of wisdom and practicality, mined out of the Vedanta, where all else had failed. Shilpkaars Vivekananda unfurls a series of events that shaped the man and Shekhar Sens dramatic rendition of it holds it up for public appraisal that is well deserved.																								Event: A musical monoact by Shekhar Sen																								When: Today at 6 pm																								Where: Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Vivekananda Hall
